<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-03-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-03-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="72" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d72">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Sanford</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 165.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-03-25"><hi rend="italic">March</hi> 25, 1865.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I enclose for your information a copy of a
                            late instruction addressed to Mr. Bigelow, and also to Messrs. Adams,
                            Perry and Wood, relative to the pirate Stonewall, otherwise Olinde or
                            Stoerkodder.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Henry S. Sanford,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., Brussels.</hi></p>
                            <p>(For enclosure see despatch No. 1302 to Mr. Adams.)</p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>